UID:10000483-1784451600-1784458800@unitedindians.org
SUMMARY:2nd Annual Indian Days 5K Run & Walk
DESCRIPTION:Join us on the final day of the 37th Annual Seafair Indian Days Powwow weekend for a morning of health\, wellness\, and community spirit! Whether you want to set a personal record or enjoy a scenic walk with the family\, the 2nd Annual Indian Days 5K Run & Walk is the perfect way to kick off the last day of celebrations.  \n\nThis event is open to everyone and is designed to bring our community together:\n Meeting Spot: Gather at the entrance to the Powwow Grounds Free Admission: No registration is needed and there is no fee to participate Fuel Up: Complimentary snacks and drinks will be provided for all participants Powwow Finale: Stay after the run to enjoy the final day of the 37th Annual Powwow
URL:https://unitedindians.org/event/2nd-annual-indian-days-5k-run-walk/
LOCATION:Daybreak Star Indian Cultural Center\, 5011 Bernie Whitebear Way\, Seattle\, WA\, 98199\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://unitedindians.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2026-Indian-Days-5k-Print-Flyer.png
END:VEVENT
